    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen `filetype off` is set in the init script, it is overridden after the init script runs.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\r\n$ cat <<'EOF' > init.vim\r\nfiletype off\r\nfiletype plugin off\r\nfiletype indent off\r\nEOF\r\n\r\n$ nvim --clean -u init.vim\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen you type `:filetype`, the output is `filetype detection:ON  plugin:OFF  indent:OFF`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nthe expected output is `filetype detection:OFF  plugin:OFF  indent:OFF`\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, 8.1.1847\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nMac OS X\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nInstalled via brew, and built from source. Also tested built from source on Ubuntu LTS.",
